## 5. Dry-Run Scope

The future dry-run scope, if later approved, is limited to non-production validation of snapshot selection and safety behavior.

Expected focus areas include:

- deterministic source selection
- fallback behavior
- malformed input handling
- stale data handling
- missing or insufficient depth handling
- symbol mismatch rejection or safe degradation
- normalized output consistency
- readiness classification
- anomaly detection and escalation

The dry-run scope excludes:

- live exchange connectivity
- real account credentials
- order placement
- order routing
- production deployment
- unattended runtime
- scheduler-based execution
