## 7. Required Preconditions Before Any Future Dry-Run

No dry-run may occur unless all of the following are true:

- [ ] Human audit has been completed
- [ ] Dry-run eligibility has been explicitly granted by an authorized human reviewer
- [ ] `s43.py` hash has been re-verified against the sealed SHA256
- [ ] Sandbox or simulation-only environment has been confirmed
- [ ] Live trading credentials are absent
- [ ] External order routing is disabled
- [ ] Production deployment targets are disconnected
- [ ] Scheduler or supervisor execution is disabled
- [ ] Logs and evidence capture are enabled
- [ ] Stop / abort procedure has been reviewed
- [ ] Dry-run operator and reviewer are identified
- [ ] Evidence storage path is defined

If any precondition is not satisfied, dry-run must not proceed.

---

## 8. Mandatory Stop Conditions

Any future dry-run must stop immediately if any of the following is observed:

- stale data appears ready
- malformed data appears ready
- partial or insufficient depth appears ready when depth is required
- conflicting source data is accepted without safe degradation
- selected winning source cannot be explained deterministically
- requested symbol and returned symbol do not match safely
- fallback behavior contradicts documented expectations
- normalized output contains inconsistent bid, ask, midpoint, spread, or timestamp fields
- logs are insufficient to reconstruct the decision
- any path indicates possible live execution capability
- environment isolation becomes uncertain

If a stop condition occurs:

1. halt remaining scenarios
2. preserve all logs and inputs
3. mark the scenario as escalated
4. notify the authorized human reviewer
5. do not continue without explicit review

